CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 6, 1956, pg. A10 reads: "Signing Register - Among those waiting to sign the register at the Council of Churches' new building, Oct. 24, when the ribbon was cut and the building officially accepted as the Protestant headquarters of the Pittsburgh Area were Mrs. Evelyn J. Brooks and Mrs. Mary Ringgold of Clark Memorial Church, Homestead. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Men, and women, including Evelyn J. Brooks and Mary Ringgold, waiting to sign register in the new Council of Churches' building
